items.title: Trump 'not confident' Israel-Gaza ceasefire will hold
items.description: The newly sworn-in US President was asked for his thoughts on the ceasefire as it enters its third day.

items.title: US trades Taliban prisoner for two American detainees
items.description: Two Americans held by the Taliban were exchanged for an Afghan imprisoned in the US on narco-terrorism charges.

items.title: Musk responds to backlash over gesture at Trump rally
items.description: The billionaire says his critics "need better dirty tricks" after a gesture likened to a Nazi salute.

items.title: South Korea president denies ordering arrest of MPs
items.description: Yoon Suk Yeol has made his first appearance at an impeachment trial which will decide if he should be permanently removed.

items.title: Ten dead in ski resort fire at Turkish hotel
items.description: At least two of the victims died after jumping from the hotel's windows, reports said.
